==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wite
<hw>Wite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>w⟦imac⟧tan</ets>; akin to D. <ets>wijten</ets>, G.
ver<ets>weisen</ets>, Icel. <ets>v⟦imac⟧ta</ets> to mulct, and E.
<ets>wit</ets>; cf. AS. <ets>w⟦imac⟧tan</ets> to see, L.
animad<ets>vertere</ets> to observe, to punish. <?/<?/<?/<?/. See
<er>Wit</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <def>To reproach; to blame; to
censure; also, to impute as blame.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Scot.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Though that I be jealous, <qex>wite</qex> me not.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There if that I misspeak or say,⟦br⟧
<qex>Wite</qex> it the ale of Southwark, I you pray.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wite</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wite
<hw>Wite</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>w⟦imac⟧te</ets> punishment.
<?/<?/<?/<?/. See <er>Wite</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <def>Blame;
reproach.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Scot.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Witeless</ent>⟦br⟧
